<taxonomicName id="52CCAF9EFFDCFF87D1AF7527FD72F9F1" authority="Pilsbry, 1897" authorityName="Pilsbry" authorityYear="1897" box="[452,764,1564,1590]" class="Bivalvia" family="Corbulidae" genus="Corbula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myoida" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="lyoni">
<emphasis id="A7B8080FFFDCFF87D1AF7527FDEEF9F1" box="[452,608,1564,1590]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Corbula lyoni</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="F15DA9ECFFDCFF87D20D7527FD72F9F1" author="Pilsbry, H. A." box="[614,764,1564,1590]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" pagination="290 - 298" refId="ref41328" refString="Pilsbry, H. A. (1897) New species of molluscs from Uruguay. Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Science of Philadelphia, 49, 290 - 298, pls. 6 - 7." type="journal article" year="1897">Pilsbry, 1897</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<collectionCode id="F3DD4CD8FFDCFF87D36E7527FCC2F9F1" box="[773,844,1564,1590]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34784" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34784" name="Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">ANSP</collectionCode>
70538, 
<emphasis id="A7B8080FFFDCFF87D3CD7527FB67F9F1" bold="true" box="[934,1257,1564,1590]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
<typeStatus id="4A776ABFFFDCFF87D3CD7527FB9FF9F1" box="[934,1041,1564,1590]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">lectotype</typeStatus>
designated herein
</emphasis>
, open pair, 12.7 mm length, 7.9 mm height; 
<collectingRegion id="57081AFFFFDCFF87D1BE757BFDDBF99D" box="[469,597,1600,1626]" country="Uruguay" name="Maldonado" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Maldonado</collectingRegion>
Bay, 
<collectingCountry id="EDDB948DFFDCFF87D2FC757AFD77F99C" box="[663,761,1601,1627]" name="Uruguay" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Uruguay</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="0DF7C898FFDCFF87D361757BFCD7F99D" box="[778,857,1600,1626]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="43.[151,250,1132,1156]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1108]" captionTargetId="figure-15@43.[151,1436,181,1108]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="FIGURE 13. Tenuicorbula lyoni (Pilsbry, 1897). A–D. ANSP 70538, lectotype designated herein. A. external view of left valve. B. internal view of left valve. C. external view of right valve. D. internal view of right valve. E–J. CIB 1104. E. external view of left valve. F. internal view of left valve. G. external view of right valve. H. internal view of right valve. I. hinge of left valve. J. hinge of right valve. K. CIB 1102, dorsal view. Scale bars:A–H= 3mm; I–J= 1mm; K= 2mm. Legends: c= chondrophore; cs= cardinal socket; ct= cardinal tooth; k= knob; ke= keel; ps= pallial sinus; rs= resilial socket." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4407182" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4407182/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
A–D); 
<typeStatus id="4A776ABFFFDCFF87D3C0757BFBCCF99D" box="[939,1090,1600,1626]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">paralectotype</typeStatus>
in the same lot, open pair, 8.6 mm length, 4.9 mm height. Pilsbry (1987) indicated the measurement of two specimens, one with 11.75 mm length and the other with 12.75 mm length. However, the 
<typeStatus id="4A776ABFFFDCFF87D2B275B2FCBEF964" box="[729,816,1673,1699]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">syntype</typeStatus>
lot of the Academy of Natural Science of Philadelphia has two specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="52CCAF9EFFDCFF87D1E67597FDA6F901" authorityName="Pilsbry" authorityYear="1897" box="[397,552,1708,1734]" class="Bivalvia" family="Corbulidae" genus="Corbula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myoida" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="lyoni">
<emphasis id="A7B8080FFFDCFF87D1E67597FDA6F901" box="[397,552,1708,1734]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Corbula lyoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and a right valve of 
<taxonomicName id="52CCAF9EFFDCFF87D3667597FC1BF901" authorityName="C. B. Adams" authorityYear="1852" box="[781,917,1708,1734]" class="Bivalvia" family="Corbulidae" genus="Corbula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myoida" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="dietziana">
<emphasis id="A7B8080FFFDCFF87D3667597FC1BF901" box="[781,917,1708,1734]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">C. dietziana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The largest specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="52CCAF9EFFDCFF87D4D97597FA84F901" authorityName="Pilsbry" authorityYear="1897" box="[1202,1290,1708,1734]" class="Bivalvia" family="Corbulidae" genus="Corbula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myoida" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="lyoni">
<emphasis id="A7B8080FFFDCFF87D4D97597FA84F901" box="[1202,1290,1708,1734]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">C. lyoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, chosen here as 
<typeStatus id="4A776ABFFFDCFF87D0DE75EBFE91F92D" box="[181,287,1744,1770]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">lectotype</typeStatus>
, is probably one of the specimens measured by Pilsbry and used for the drawing on plate VII, due to the similarity between the number and shape of the ribs represented in his design with the specimen. The other specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="52CCAF9EFFDCFF87D0867423FECBF8F5" authorityName="Pilsbry" authorityYear="1897" box="[237,325,1816,1842]" class="Bivalvia" family="Corbulidae" genus="Corbula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myoida" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="lyoni">
<emphasis id="A7B8080FFFDCFF87D0867423FECBF8F5" box="[237,325,1816,1842]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">C. lyoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was not measured by Pilsbry, as it is 8.6 mm. The second specimen measured by Pilsbry may have been the right valve of 
<taxonomicName id="52CCAF9EFFDCFF87D1F17407FDACF891" authorityName="C. B. Adams" authorityYear="1852" box="[410,546,1852,1878]" class="Bivalvia" family="Corbulidae" genus="Corbula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myoida" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="dietziana">
<emphasis id="A7B8080FFFDCFF87D1F17407FDACF891" box="[410,546,1852,1878]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">C. dietziana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
