</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="DDD68796FFDFFF84D0AC7542FA16F876" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="9573D41DFFDFFF84D0AC7542FE3BF881" blockId="42.[151,1437,151,1970]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis id="A7B8080FFFDFFF84D0AC7542FEBAF954" bold="true" box="[199,308,1657,1683]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Remarks</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName id="52CCAF9EFFDFFF84D12D7542FD93F954" baseAuthorityName="Pilsbry" baseAuthorityYear="1897" box="[326,541,1657,1683]" class="Bivalvia" family="Corbulidae" genus="Tenuicorbula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myoida" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="lyoni">
<emphasis id="A7B8080FFFDFFF84D12D7542FD93F954" box="[326,541,1657,1683]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Tenuicorbula lyoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="52CCAF9EFFDFFF84D34E7542FAA1F954" authority="(G. B. Sowerby I, 1833)" baseAuthorityName="G. B. Sowerby I" baseAuthorityYear="1833" box="[805,1327,1657,1683]" class="Bivalvia" family="Corbulidae" genus="Tenuicorbula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myoida" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="tenuis">
<emphasis id="A7B8080FFFDFFF84D34E7542FB89F954" box="[805,1031,1657,1683]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Tenuicorbula tenuis</emphasis>
(G. B. Sowerby I, 1833)
</taxonomicName>
from the Eastern Pacific by its sculpture, escutcheon and dorsal margin. 
<taxonomicName id="52CCAF9EFFDFFF84D33775A7FBBEF971" baseAuthorityName="Pilsbry" baseAuthorityYear="1897" box="[860,1072,1692,1718]" class="Bivalvia" family="Corbulidae" genus="Tenuicorbula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myoida" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="lyoni">
<emphasis id="A7B8080FFFDFFF84D33775A7FBBEF971" box="[860,1072,1692,1718]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Tenuicorbula lyoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a wide commarginal ribs on the central slope and narrower commarginal ribs on the posterior slope, the escutcheon is narrow and the posterior dorsal margin is straight and ventrally inclined; 
<taxonomicName id="52CCAF9EFFDFFF84D2C175DEFC86F939" baseAuthorityName="G. B. Sowerby I" baseAuthorityYear="1833" box="[682,776,1765,1790]" class="Bivalvia" family="Corbulidae" genus="Tenuicorbula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myoida" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="tenuis">
<emphasis id="A7B8080FFFDFFF84D2C175DEFC86F939" box="[682,776,1765,1790]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">T. tenuis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have fine and dense commarginal ribs on the beaks, central and posterior slope (
<bibRefCitation id="F15DA9ECFFDFFF84D1137433FE79F8E5" author="Coan, E. V." box="[376,503,1800,1826]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" pagination="47 - 105" refId="ref37458" refString="Coan, E. V. (2002) The Eastern Pacific recent species of the Corbulidae (Bivalvia). Malacologia, 44 (1), 47 - 105" type="journal article" year="2002">Coan 2002</bibRefCitation>
), a comparatively wider escutcheon, principally on the left valve, and their posterior dorsal margin is concave.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9573D41DFFDFFF84D0AC7474FA16F876" blockId="42.[151,1437,151,1970]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
<bibRefCitation id="F15DA9ECFFDFFF84D0AC7474FEE4F8AE" author="Ihering, H." box="[199,362,1871,1897]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" pagination="1 - 611" refId="ref39278" refString="Ihering, H. (1907) Les mollusques fossils du Tertiaire et du Cretace Superieur de l'Argentine. Anales del Museo Nacional de Buenos Aires, 14 (7), 1 - 611, 18 ps." type="journal article" year="1907">Ihering (1907)</bibRefCitation>
included 
<taxonomicName id="52CCAF9EFFDFFF84D1B3746BFDA2F8AE" baseAuthorityName="Pilsbry" baseAuthorityYear="1897" box="[472,556,1871,1897]" class="Bivalvia" family="Corbulidae" genus="Tenuicorbula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myoida" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="lyoni">
<emphasis id="A7B8080FFFDFFF84D1B3746BFDA2F8AE" box="[472,556,1871,1897]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">T. lyoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="52CCAF9EFFDFFF84D3517474FB23F8AE" authority="Philippi, 1893" authorityName="Philippi" authorityYear="1893" box="[826,1197,1871,1897]" class="Bivalvia" family="Corbulidae" genus="Corbula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myoida" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="pulchella">
<emphasis id="A7B8080FFFDFFF84D3517474FB89F8AE" box="[826,1031,1871,1897]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Corbula pulchella</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="F15DA9ECFFDFFF84D4657474FB23F8AE" author="Philippi, R. A." box="[1038,1197,1871,1897]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" pagination="5 - 16" refId="ref41293" refString="Philippi, R. A. (1893) Descripcion de algunos fosiles terciarios de la Republica Argentina. Anales del Museo Nacional de Chile, 3, 5 - 16, 4 pls." type="journal article" year="1893">Philippi, 1893</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and this decision has been followed by 
<bibRefCitation id="F15DA9ECFFDFFF84D1367448FE7BF84A" author="Huber, M." box="[349,501,1907,1933]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" refId="ref39198" refString="Huber, M. (2010) Compendium of bivalves. A full-color guide to 3,300 of the world's marine bivalves. A status on Bivalvia after 250 years of research. ConchBooks, Hackenheim, 901 pp. [CD-ROM]" type="book" year="2010">Huber (2010)</bibRefCitation>
. After exhaustive searches of many museums, I was unable to find the 
<typeStatus id="4A776ABFFFDFFF84D4947448FAD1F84A" box="[1279,1375,1907,1933]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="52CCAF9EFFDFFF84D5E8744FFF73F876" authorityName="Philippi" authorityYear="1893" class="Bivalvia" family="Corbulidae" genus="Corbula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myoida" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="pulchella">
<emphasis id="A7B8080FFFDFFF84D5E8744FFF73F876" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">C. pulchella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to confirm the synonymy. Philippi’s description for 
<taxonomicName id="52CCAF9EFFDFFF84D35274A3FC31F876" authorityName="Philippi" authorityYear="1893" box="[825,959,1943,1970]" class="Bivalvia" family="Corbulidae" genus="Corbula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myoida" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="pulchella">
<emphasis id="A7B8080FFFDFFF84D35274A3FC31F876" box="[825,959,1943,1970]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">C. pulchella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is succinct and the figure is uninformative.
</paragraph>
